Debbie- I was a patient in Menlo Park for six months.  If you want to know what goes on in that program, I can tell you what I observed, but its been a long time for me. I will tell you this from my experiences. A part of the program deals with the vet reliving his experiences and trying to make sense of it. The unfortunate part is that it rips one to shreds and before you know it, you are on the street bleeding like a stuck pig. It takes time for closure for the open wounds. Three month programs cannot accomodate the vets through this time. While at Menlo Park, emphasis was on making sure there was a support system when a vet goes home just for this reason. A wife is not enough support no matter how much she loves her husband, because it is a big load for one to deal with. You end up with you own set of problems. I strongly suggest you follow Doc Spatz's advice and seek help for both you sakes. Your first stop should be at a vet center and they can help you find resources. If not, then you'll have to try the private sector. Good luck to both of you. E-mail me if you want.
